The paper deals with denoising using minimum description length (MDL) criterion, which is a statistical approach to model selection. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories in computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), signal processing (cs.SP), and statistics (cs.ST). However, since the paper focuses on wavelet-based denoising, which is a common technique in image and signal processing, we can further narrow down the likely sub-categories to cs.CV, cs.SI, and cs.SP.
